    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-02-07T10:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-02-07T10:30:00-05:00" n="560"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d560">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">840.48 Refugees/4934: Airgram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-02-07T11:30:00-04:00"
                            >February 7, 1944—11:30 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>A–45. On December 24, 1943 Department received a note from the Polish
                        Embassy<note n="29" xml:id="d560fn29">Not printed.</note> stating that the
                    Polish Minister at Bern had received information that the Spanish Ambassador in
                    Berlin, acting upon instructions from the Government of Paraguay, intended to
                    annul passports theretofore issued by the Paraguayan Consul in Bern to Polish
                    Jews who were interned by the Germans in special camps for citizens of the
                    Allied Nations. As a result on December 12 German authorities arrived at camps
                    and took up passports of all Allied Governments held by Jews. Department desires
                    that you place matter <pb facs="1006" n="992" xml:id="pg_992"/> before Swiss
                    Foreign Office requesting that appropriate Swiss consular officers in Germany
                    make an investigation in the matter. If any American passports have been taken
                    up it is desired that if possible the Swiss consular officers obtain the names
                    of the persons to whom they were issued, the approximate date of issue and make
                    appropriate representations with a view to having passports surrendered to Swiss
                    consular officers for ultimate transmission to the Department.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
